# Git Configuration

Always use the following git identity for commits and pushes in this repository.

<rule>
name: git_config_identity
description: Enforce consistent git user configuration for all commits

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      ### Git Identity for This Repository

      **Always use these credentials when committing or pushing:**

      ```bash
      git config user.name "charmas3r"
      git config user.email "evansmith0115@gmail.com"
      ```

      ### Commit & Push Workflow

      When committing changes:
      ```bash
      git add .
      git commit -m "Your commit message"
      git push origin main
      ```

      ### Remote Repository
      - **Repository:** https://github.com/charmas3r/cursor-website.git
      - **Branch:** main

      ### Important
      - Always verify the git config is set before committing
      - Use descriptive commit messages
      - Push to the `main` branch

examples:
  - input: |
      # Committing changes
      git config user.name "charmas3r"
      git config user.email "evansmith0115@gmail.com"
      git add .
      git commit -m "Add new feature"
      git push origin main
    output: "Correctly configured git push"

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
